<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>The managing editor of conservative website RedState, who published under a pseudonym multiple articles attacking Dr Anthony Fauci, has been revealed as a press officer working for Fauci's agency.</p>

<p>The National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Diseases confirmed on Monday that William B. Crews had resigned, after his alias was uncovered.</p>

<p>Crews was writing under the name Streiff, and, fervently opposed to COVID-19 guidance on face masks, called his boss an 'attention-grabbing and media-whoring mask Nazi'.</p>

<p>Crews' identity was first reported by Daily Beast.</p>

<p>A public information officer working for Dr Fauci's institute has been outed as a secret critic</p>

<p>'NIAID first learned of this matter this morning, and Mr. Crews has informed us of his intention to retire,' a spokesman told CNN. </p>

<p>'We have no further comments on this as it is a personnel matter.' </p>

<p>By Monday afternoon Crews had been removed from NIAID's internal directory. </p>

<p>On his Twitter account, Crews describes himself as: 'Managing Editor at RedState.com, Former Infantry officer, CGSC grad, Army staff. Pronouns: F***/You.'</p>
